-- U.K. Stocks Advance as FTSE 100 Index Rebounds
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2013-07-29T09:10:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-29/u-k-stocks-advance-as-ftse-100-index-rebounds.html
 U.K. stocks rose for the first time
in three days, with the FTSE 100 Index rebounding from its first
weekly decline this month, as WPP Plc rallied.  WPP rose 2.4 percent after Publicis Groupe SA and Omnicom
Group Inc. agreed to merge and create the world’s largest
advertising company. Elan Corp. jumped 10 percent to its highest
price since July 2008 in Dublin after Perrigo Co. agreed to buy
the Irish drugmaker. Ryanair Holdings Plc fell 2.5 percent as
first-quarter profit dropped 21 percent. Barclays Plc slid 2.7
percent after a report that it is considering a 4 billion-pound
($6.2 billion) share sale.  The FTSE 100 added 24.66 points, or 0.4 percent, to
6,579.45 at 10:09 a.m. in  London . The benchmark gauge retreated
1.1 percent last week, ending four consecutive weeks of gains.
The broader FTSE All-Share Index rose 0.3 percent today, while
Ireland’s ISEQ Index gained 0.8 percent.  In the U.S., a report at 10 a.m.  New York  time may show
pending house sales slipped 1 percent in June, after climbing
6.7 percent the previous month, according to the median forecast
of 34 economists in a Bloomberg survey.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
